2026-03-21T16:18:13.516Z JOY-001E item.created "Kanban-style board view as default for joy command" [horst.schwarz@joydev.com]
2026-03-21T16:18:22.006Z JOY-001E comment.added "Plan: Rewrite crates/joy-cli/src/commands/board.rs. (1) Header: project name from project.yaml, created date from oldest item or project init, last change from event log, total item count. (2) Columns: one per status that has items, empty stati as 1-char thin column. Distribute terminal width proportionally by item count. (3) Items: adaptive layout -- wide (>30 cols): ID+emojis+title one line; medium (20-30): ID+emojis line 1, title line 2; narrow (<20): ID line 1, emojis line 2. No blank lines between items in wide mode. (4) Height: terminal height - 3, truncate with '...' per column, --all disables limit. (5) Footer: summary line (open/in-progress/closed/blocked counts). (6) Borders: dashed lines matching joy ls style." [horst.schwarz@joydev.com]
2026-03-21T16:18:28.656Z JOY-001E item.status_changed "new -> in-progress" [horst.schwarz@joydev.com]
2026-03-21T16:49:19.690Z JOY-001F item.created "config set accepts invalid values, load_config silently falls back to defaults" [horst.schwarz@joydev.com]
2026-03-21T16:49:25.800Z JOY-001F comment.added "Two related issues: (1) config set accepts any value without schema validation -- e.g. 'joy config set output.color false' stores a boolean, but ColorMode expects auto/always/never. (2) load_config in store.rs uses unwrap_or_default on deserialization, silently returning the full default config when any field has an invalid type. Combined effect: setting one field to an invalid value resets the entire config to defaults without warning." [horst.schwarz@joydev.com]
2026-03-21T16:49:37.491Z JOY-001F item.status_changed "new -> in-progress" [horst.schwarz@joydev.com]
2026-03-21T16:50:32.085Z JOY-001F comment.added "Fixed: (A) load_config now warns to stderr instead of silently falling back to defaults. (B) config set validates the merged config against the Config struct before writing -- rejects invalid values with a clear error message." [horst.schwarz@joydev.com]
2026-03-21T16:50:32.087Z JOY-001F item.status_changed "in-progress -> closed" [horst.schwarz@joydev.com]
